race.comment: A host of key scratchings make a tough race a lot clearer. The lightly raced LONG LEGS (6) who resumes from a three-month spell now gets the nod. Opened last prep with a soft all-the-way win over this trip at Rosehill. Went to the Group 3 Spring Stakes at Newcastle after that and did a fine job to hold on for third after racing handy. Trialled well at Canterbury recently - looks to be in for a big campaign. PROFOUNDLY (9) last appeared when an eye-catching fourth in the 1400m Reginald Allen Quality at Group 3 level on 18 October. Wasn't beaten far first-up last prep in a strong three-year-old race at Eagle Farm. Right in contention. SNITZEL DANCER (10) battled on evenly without threatening first-up over 1200m here. Better placed out to this trip so a likely improver. AUTUMN DREAM (7) is back from a 27-week spell. Turned in some handy performances last time in work including a first-up placing over today's distance at Newcastle. Should be thereabouts. TOTOKA (8) best of the rest.
